column4: Gives the time when he will get the information (e.g. “We will give that information in the brief this afternoon”)
column6: Displays understanding and empathy towards the officer and his need to know and does not dismiss the concern (e.g. “I appreciate you looking out for your team” rather than “I’m too busy”)
column8: Explains that you are not ready (e.g. “Not all details have been finalized” or "I am preparing for the brief")
